 forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."]},{"name":"Albert","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Albert</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Dafydd ap Ieuan was born about 1337, in Darowen, Montgomeryshire, Wales, his father, Ieuaf Goch Llywelyn, was 49 and his mother, Mrs. Ieuaf Goch Llywelyn, was 1209. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1337–":"umbes 1337–Surnud","1328–Male":"1328–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1333–Male":"1333–Surnud","1336–Female":"1336–Surnud","1337–Male":"1337–Surnud","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1342–Male":"1342–Surnud","1345–Male":"1345–Surnud","1367–Female":"1367–Surnud","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","0129–Female":"0129–Surnud","1337":"1337","1336":"1336","1367":"1367","1345":"1345","1333":"1333","about 1337":"umbes 1337","1342":"1342","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","0129":"0129","1290":"1290","1328":"1328","{Blddn ap Cnfn}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Itaalia","Darowen, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Darowen, Montgomeryshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1337–":"noin 1337–Kuollut","1328–Male":"1328–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1333–Male":"1333–Kuollut","1336–Female":"1336–Kuollut","1337–Male":"1337–Kuollut","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1342–Male":"1342–Kuollut","1345–Male":"1345–Kuollut","1367–Female":"1367–Kuollut","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","0129–Female":"0129–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1336":"1336","1367":"1367","1345":"1345","1333":"1333","about 1337":"noin 1337","1342":"1342","1330"